Mike Anderson wrote:
> If you would have ordered a panel from the factory with the sliding door 
> option, would it be a sliding door with no windows?  Did VW make such a 
> door?

The sliding door was an option on all but the pickups:

M-Code: Translation
069: middle and rear seats in passenger area with masonite door panels, for kombi with left-hand sliding door
142: sliding door on both sides
142: sliding door on both sides
145: sliding door safety latch
161: Sliding door Types 211, 213, 214
162: sliding door (on both sides?) Types 215, 216
163: Sliding door Types 221-228
164: Sliding door Types 241, 244 after 1960,  front turn signals until 1/60
165: sliding door with front blinkers
169: Sliding door Types 231-238
211: seating for 9 people (double sliding doors)
520: sliding doors left and right
529: glass divider with sliding window

Models:

237:Kombi, Sliding Door Right, LHD
238:Kombi, Sliding Door Left, RHD

